==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pollock
<hw>Pol"lock</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Pollack</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A marine gadoid fish
(<spn>Pollachius carbonarius</spn>), native both of the European and
American coasts. It is allied to the cod, and like it is salted and
dried. In England it is called <altname>coalfish</altname>,
<altname>lob</altname>, <altname>podley</altname>,
<altname>podling</altname>, <altname>pollack</altname>, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pollucite</ent>⟦br⟧
